# 🚀 Intro to AI & ML in 10 Minutes

> If you're wondering what AI/ML really means — this is your crash course 🧠⚡

---

## 🧠 What is AI?
AI = Artificial Intelligence  
Machines that can simulate **thinking, decision-making, and learning**.

Examples: Siri, Alexa, ChatGPT, self-driving cars, Google Search

---

## 🧠 What is Machine Learning?
ML is a subfield of AI where machines learn from **data** instead of being explicitly programmed.

ML uses **patterns in data** to make predictions or decisions.

---

## 🔍 Common ML Types

| Type | Example | Use |
|------|---------|-----|
| Supervised | Predict prices, spam detection | Has labels |
| Unsupervised | Group similar users | No labels |
| Reinforcement | Self-driving car learns rules | Learns via rewards |

---

## 📈 Real-Life Examples

- YouTube Recommendations
- Face Unlock
- Stock Market Predictions
- Cyber Threat Detection

---

